{"type":"message","id":"b67723aa","parentId":"b2b08854","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:07:15.561Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-09 20:07 EST] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: # TASK: Evaluate OC-Respawner for Full Real Capability\n\n## CONTEXT\nThe `OC-Respawner` skill is currently classified as PARTIAL because:\n- Not fully evaluated\n- Unknown real capability\n- Unknown if can perform real environment validation and respawn decisions\n\n## YOUR MISSION\nEvaluate `OC-Respawner` for FULL real capability and prove or disprove functionality.\n\n## ANTI-SIMULATION RULES (ABSOLUTE)\n- NO simulated environment validation\n- NO fake respawn decisions\n- NO placeholder evidence\n- REAL environment checks → REAL validation → REAL respawn logic\n- Evidence must be operational, not narrative\n\n## SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS\n\n### 1. Test Real Environment Validation\n- Execute real environment checks\n- Validate actual system state\n- Check prerequisites, dependencies, runtime conditions\n- Produce real validation results\n\n### 2. Test Respawn Decision Logic\n- Based on real validation results\n- Make real respawn decisions\n- Apply decision logic correctly\n- Handle different validation outcomes\n\n### 3. Test Integration Points\n- Integration with monitoring systems\n- Integration with agent lifecycle\n- Integration with error handling\n- Real handoffs and triggers\n\n### 4. Prove Operational Value\n- Show how respawner maintains system health\n- Demonstrate recovery capability\n- Provide real usage scenarios\n- Show integration with existing workflows\n\n## TEST SCENARIOS\n\n### Scenario 1: Healthy Environment Validation\n- Validate currently healthy environment\n- Confirm all checks pass\n- Verify no respawn needed\n\n### Scenario 2: Simulated Failure Validation\n- Introduce controlled validation failures (where safe)\n- Test respawn decision logic\n- Verify appropriate responses\n\n### Scenario 3: Integration Testing\n- Test integration with monitoring\n- Test integration with agent lifecycle\n- Test handoff to other components\n\n## EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS\n\n### Must Provide:\n1. **Real environment validation results** - Actual system checks\n2. **Real respawn decision evidence** - Based on validation\n3. **Integration test results** - With other components\n4. **Operational scenarios** - Real usage examples\n5. **Capability assessment** - What works, what doesn't\n\n### Must NOT Provide:\n- Simulated validation\n- Fake decisions\n- Placeholder evidence\n- Theoretical capability claims\n\n## SUCCESS CRITERIA\n`OC-Respawner` classification depends on results:\n\n### FUNCTIONAL if:\n1. Real environment validation works\n2. Real respawn decision logic works\n3. Integration points functional\n4. Evidence shows real operational capability\n\n### PARTIAL if:\n1. Some functions work but limitations exist\n2. Real capability proven but incomplete\n3. Honest classification required\n\n### SIMULATED if:\n1. No real validation occurs\n2. Fake decisions or placeholder evidence\n3. Documentation-only capability\n\n## TIMELINE\n- Start: Immediate\n- Complete: Within 20 minutes\n- Report: Concise with operational evidence and honest classification\n\nProceed to evaluate REAL capability."}],"timestamp":1773104835558}}
{"type":"message","id":"493c1272","parentId":"b67723aa","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:07:22.221Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'll evaluate the OC-Respawner skill for real capability. Let me start by reading the skill documentation to understand its design and implementation."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_nqHlKLlA19QRPYy07c9stc63","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-Respawner/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":11800,"output":88,"cacheRead":2304,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14192,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773104835560}}
{"type":"message","id":"ae6888b7","parentId":"493c1272","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:07:22.240Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_nqHlKLlA19QRPYy07c9stc63","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: oc-respawner\ndescription: A self-documenting migration system that analyzes, documents, tracks, and reconstructs the OpenClaw environment on a new machine through non-destructive observation, host-aware migration logic, and deterministic reconstruction.\ncategory: system\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: model\nrequires: [\"python\", \"bash\"]\noptional_requires: [\"postgresql\"]\nsafety-level: high\nwrap-up-enabled: false\n---\n\n# OC-Respawner Skill\n\n## Purpose\nA self-documenting migration system that analyzes, documents, tracks, and reconstructs the OpenClaw environment on a new machine (target: macOS / Mac Mini).\n\n## Design Principles\n1. **Non‑destructive observation** - Only observe, never modify existing systems\n2. **Host‑aware migration logic** - Detect current OS (Linux) vs target OS (macOS)\n3. **Security‑first** - Never store API keys or secrets in knowledge base\n4. **Deterministic reconstruction** - Same input should produce same output\n5. **Incremental maintenance** - Support daily updates to knowledge base\n6. **Structured data first** - Use JSON + Markdown for knowledge base\n\n## Skill Structure\n```\nskills/OC-Respawner/\n├── SKILL.md (this file)\n├── scripts/\n│   ├── scan_environment.py\n│   ├── build_registry.py\n│   ├── build_inventory.py\n│   ├── build_playbook.py\n│   ├── detect_changes.py\n│   ├── classify_dependencies.py\n│   ├── generate_gap_report.py\n│   ├── reconstruct_environment.py\n│   └── validate_environment.py\n├── references/\n│   ├── INVENTORY_SCHEMA.md\n│   ├── MIGRATION_RULES.md\n│   ├── CLASSIFICATION_RULES.md\n│   └── MACOS_INSTALL_GUIDE.md\n└── examples/\n    ├── example_registry.md\n    └── example_playbook.md\n```\n\n## Runtime Knowledge Base\n```\nworkspace/system_knowledge/\n├── SYSTEM_REGISTRY.md\n├── SYSTEM_INVENTORY.json\n├── MIGRATION_PLAYBOOK.md\n├── SYSTEM_CHANGELOG.md\n└── MIGRATION_GAP_REPORT.md\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### Phase 1: Baseline Analysis\n```bash\n# Run full baseline analysis\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-Respawner/scripts/scan_environment.py\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-Respawner/scripts/build_registry.py\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-Respawner/scripts/build_inventory.py\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-Respawner/scripts/build_playbook.py\n```\n\n### Phase 2: Daily Maintenance\n```bash\n# Detect changes and update knowledge base\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-Respawner/scripts/detect_changes.py\n```\n\n### Phase 3: Reconstruction (when requested)\n```bash\n# Generate gap report and guide reconstruction\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-Respawner/scripts/generate_gap_report.py\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-Respawner/scripts/reconstruct_environment.py\n```\n\n## Classification Rules\nEach component is classified as one or more of:\n- `portable` - Can be copied directly\n- `host_specific` - Requires OS-specific installation\n- `reinstall_required` - Must be reinstalled on target\n- `secret_required` - Requires API keys/secrets (not stored)\n- `optional` - Not critical for operation\n- `critical` - Essential for OpenClaw operation\n\n## System Components Inventoried\n- OpenClaw workspace (skills, references, memory, tools, scripts)\n- Automation (cron jobs, scheduled agents)\n- Core systems (PostgreSQL, pgvector, Python environment)\n- AI services (Tavily, Firecrawl, Gemini embeddings)\n- Monitoring (watchdog, janitor, error-learning-loop)\n\n## Target Platform: macOS (Mac Mini)\nRequired tools:\n- Homebrew (package manager)\n- Git\n- Python 3.13+\n- pip\n- PostgreSQL 15+\n- pgvector extension\n\n## Integration with Existing Ecosystem\n- **Watchdog**: Register long-running scans\n- **Error-learning-loop**: Report migration incidents\n- **Workspace-janitor**: Clean old knowledge base files\n- **Memory system**: Store migration patterns in vector DB\n\n## Incident Patterns\n- `migration|FAILURE|missing_dependency`\n- `migration|FAILURE|db_not_running`\n- `migration|FAILURE|cron_missing`\n- `migration|DEGRADED|api_key_missing`\n\n## Validation Checks\n- PostgreSQL running\n- pgvector installed\n- Python dependencies installed\n- Skills directory valid\n- Vector memory searchable\n- Cron active\n- Watchdog running\n- Learning loop running\n- Janitor running\n\n## Security Constraints\n1. **Never store secrets** - API keys, passwords, or credentials\n2. **Non-destructive** - Only observe existing systems\n3. **Host-aware** - Adapt to current vs target OS differences\n4. **Incremental** - Support daily knowledge base updates\n5. **Deterministic** - Consistent output from same input\n\n## Quick Start\n1. Run baseline analysis:\n   ```bash\n   cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-Respawner\n   python scripts/scan_environment.py\n   ```\n2. Review generated knowledge base in `~/.openclaw/workspace/system_knowledge/`\n3. For migration to macOS, follow `MIGRATION_PLAYBOOK.md`\n\n## Maintenance\n- Daily cron: Detect changes and update inventory\n- Weekly cron: Rebuild migration playbook and verify dependencies\n- On-demand: Generate gap reports for reconstruction"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773104842235}}
