{"type":"message","id":"dfeba07a","parentId":"09993d56","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:10:15.599Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_ng8pdCLzRlaMgAuHjAhycQLk","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CLASSIFICATION_RULES.md\n\n## Classification System\n\nEach component in the OpenClaw environment must be classified with one or more of the following labels:\n\n### 1. portable\n**Definition**: Can be copied directly from source to target without modification.\n\n**Examples**:\n- Markdown files (`.md`)\n- JSON configuration files\n- Python scripts (without system dependencies)\n- Skill directories (self-contained)\n- Memory files (`memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`)\n- Reference documents\n\n**Rules**:\n- Must not contain absolute paths\n- Must not contain system-specific configurations\n- Must be text-based (not binary)\n- Can be transferred via `rsync` or `scp`\n\n### 2. host_specific\n**Definition**: Requires OS-specific installation, configuration, or adaptation.\n\n**Examples**:\n- System packages (`apt` vs `brew`)\n- Service management (`systemd` vs `launchctl`)\n- File paths (`/home/openclaw` vs `/Users/openclaw`)\n\n[191 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773105015588}}
